public class ServiceFilterBinder.FilteringServiceBroker
extends DelegatingServiceBroker

Base class for filtering/auditing/etc services, extending DelegatingServiceBroker for security. This implementation acts as a passthrough for publish/subscribe mechanisms

Method Detail

getService

public java.lang.Object getService(java.lang.Object requestor,
                                   java.lang.Class serviceClass,
                                   ServiceRevokedListener srl)
This implementation of getService calls allowService(serviceClass). If allowService returns true, will then call getClientProxy to proxy the client, delegates to the real broker to request the service, then calls getServiceProxy to wrap the service.

Specified by:
getService in interface ServiceBroker
Overrides:
getService in class DelegatingServiceBroker

allowService

Override to control if a given service class is allowed or now

getClientProxy

protected java.lang.Object getClientProxy(java.lang.Object client,
                                          java.lang.Class serviceClass)
Override to specify an alternative instance to use as the client (requestor) object when actually requesting the service. A return value of null is interpreted as "no proxy". This implementation always returns null.

getServiceProxy

protected java.lang.Object getServiceProxy(java.lang.Object service,
                                           java.lang.Class serviceClass,
                                           java.lang.Object client)
Override to specify an alternative instance to use as the service implementation passed back to the client component. A return value of null is interpreted as "no proxy". This implementation always returns null.

Parameters:
client - is the client object passed up to the real service broker. This is usually the requestor, but may be a proxy for the requestor if getClientProxy was exercised.

releaseService

public void releaseService(java.lang.Object requestor,
                           java.lang.Class serviceClass,
                           java.lang.Object service)
As usual, releases a service previously requested from the ServiceBroker. here, we do additional work to make sure that the service implementation is actually released, regardless of the combination of proxies the binder may have provided. Calls releaseServiceProxy and releaseClientProxy as appropriate.

Specified by:
releaseService in interface ServiceBroker
Overrides:
releaseService in class DelegatingServiceBroker

releaseServiceProxy

protected void releaseServiceProxy(java.lang.Object serviceProxy,
                                   java.lang.Object service,
                                   java.lang.Class serviceClass)
Called to release a serviceProxy previously constructed by the binder. Override to change the default behavior of "do nothing". Note that this method is called before the real service is released.

releaseClientProxy

protected void releaseClientProxy(java.lang.Object clientProxy,
                                  java.lang.Object client,
                                  java.lang.Class serviceClass)
Called to release a clientProxy previously constructed by the binder. Override to change the default behavior of "do nothing". Note that this method is called after the service is released.
